<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9701] NPE in export handler when &quot;fl&quot; parameter is omitted.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9701</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This started when a user reported that if you do not specify any parameters for the export handler, you get an NPE. I tracked it down to not specifying an &quot;fl&quot; parameter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But in general I rearranged the error reporting in SortingResponseWriter.write so that immediately upon detecting a problem, the exception gets written to the output stream and then return immediately rather than save it up for the end. Preliminary version of the patch attached; it fixes the immediate problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Still to see is if it breaks any tests since the first error detected will be returned to the user rather than the last. I&apos;ll fix any tests that are sensitive to this and check in sometime this weekend.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
